Nigerian singer, David Adeleke, popularly known as Davido, has declared his passion for politics, expressing that it is in his blood. The singer disclosed this in a tweet on Saturday via his official Twitter page, responding to a new report by People’s Gazette on a court ruling in favour of Dotun Babayemi instead of his uncle, Ademola Adeleke. He wrote, ““Stop spreading this nonsense cap, State Courts don’t have jurisdiction, only Federal High Courts can handle post Primary Matters. Keep fooling y’all selves ! Anyway shutdown Manchester aka Gyalchester tonite!” BREAKING: Ademola Adeleke Declared Winner Of Osun PDP Gov… Davido Writes About His Trust In God Following his tweet, a Twitter user, Chime Fabian urged the musician to stop meddling in politics by posting, “obo, how i wish yh stayed off politics!!!” Davido responded, “Sorry it’s in my blood and it’s def my passion and it ain’t stopping SHIT!”